            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Patris et Filii et Spiritu Sancti. Hanno Deo propitjo pontificatus
                        domni nostri <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/1636">Gregorii</persName>
                        summi pontifitjs et huniversalis <rs key="#Popes">pape</rs> in apostolica
                        sacratissima beati Petri apostoli Domini sede [...]o sitque inperante domno
                            <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/7">Ottone</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">inperatore</rs> in Italia vero anno quarto, die
                        vie[simo ...] mensis octubris, ind(itjone) duodetjma, <placeName
                            ref="#places/3535">suburbio Ravenne</placeName>, foris <rs
                            key="#Clusae/gates">porta</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Clusae/gates" ref="#places/3582">[Sancti Lau]rentji qui
                            vocatur in Cesarea</placeName>, infra <rs key="#Residences"
                            >palatjum</rs> prescripti Ottonis cesaris tertji. Hec etenim ratjo ideo
                        scripturarum anotatur vinculis ut temporibus recordetur plurimis. Dum
                        inventus fuissem ego quidem <persName key="#Tabellio"><name ref="Iohannes"
                                >Ioh(anne)s</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Tabellio">tabellio</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/594">Raven[nas</placeName> infr]a ipsum palatjum et
                        ibi mecum bone hopinionis et <rs key="#Personal_rank">laudabiles fama
                            [viri]</rs>, quorum nomina [ta]li quanta ut audies nuncupative exponam:
                            <persName key="#Witness #Personal_rank"><name ref="Paulus"
                            >Paulus</name></persName> insignis vir et <persName
                            key="#Witness #Personal_rank"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petrus</name></persName> famosus dativus germanus eius, filii quondam
                                <persName><name ref="Paulus de Traversaria">Pauli qui vocabatur de
                                Traversaria</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Personal_rank"><name ref="Andreas/Uter">Andreas dativus
                                qui vocatur Uter</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Witness #Personal_rank"><name ref="Michael"
                            >Michael</name></persName> eius nat(us) et <persName
                            key="#Witness #Personal_rank"><name ref="Andreas de Severo">Andreas
                                dativus qui vocatur de Severo</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Tabellio #Personal_rank"><name ref="Andreas"
                                >Andreas</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Tabellio">tabellio</rs> filius quondam <persName key="#Tabellio"
                                ><name ref="Iohannes">Iohannis</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Tabellio">tabellionis</rs>
                        <persName key="#Witness #Tabellio #Personal_rank"><name ref="Richulfus"
                                >Riculfusque</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Tabellio">tabellio</rs> filius quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Andreas">Andreê</name></persName> et alii plures quorum nomina
                        si per omnia adscribere conatus fuero in factis quoque videbor defitjens; in
                        nostra suprascriptorum omnium presentja venerunt <persName><name
                                ref="Ghisulfus">Gisulfus</name></persName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Dominicus">Dominicus</name></persName> germani et apreenderunt
                        virgam manibus suis et miserunt illam in manus prescriptorum Pauli et Petri
                        germanorum, filiorum quondam Pauli qui vocabatur de Traversaria, et
                        dixerunt: ‘Ecce refutamus vobis <rs key="#Landed_possessions">omnes res et
                            pertinentjas nostras</rs> que nobis pertinent per quemcumque modum vel
                        titulum in quattuor <rs key="#Fundi">fundis</rs>, quorum vocabula hec sunt,
                            <geogName key="#Fundi" ref="#estates/2430"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                                >Scannus</placeName></geogName> et <geogName key="#Fundi"
                            ref="#estates/2431"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                            >Lisinianus</placeName></geogName>, <geogName key="#Fundi"
                            ref="#estates/2433"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                            >Roverit(us)</placeName></geogName> et <geogName key="#Fundi"
                            ref="#estates/2432"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                            >Perit(us)</placeName></geogName>, quantascumque in ipsis habemus, ut
                        per anc refutatjonem habeatis ip[sa]s nostras pertinentjas cum vestris
                        filiis et heredibus in perpetuum’. Statimque spoponderunt se ipsi germani
                        refutatores suosque filios et heredes composituros isdem fratribus
                        accipientibus suisque filiis et heredibus de <rs key="#Penalty">denariis
                            mancosos centum</rs>, si in aliquo tempore aliqua controversia aut
                        molestatjones de is rebus fetjssent contra ipsos acceptores aut contra eorum
                        filios vel heredes; et notitjam quam exinde fueri oportebat in suo robore
                        promiserunt permanendam et tunc dederunt eis missum nomine <persName><name
                                ref="Iohannes/Blancus">Iohannes qui vocatur
                            Blancus</name></persName> qui corporaliter eos vel eorum <rs
                            key="#Missus">missum</rs> de is rebus corporaliter investisset. Et ipsi
                        accipientes rogaverunt nos pro futuro testimonio. Hoc factum est sub die et
                        m(ense) et ind(itjone) suprascripta duodetjma, RAV(en)NE SUBURBIO.</ab>
